`crates/ctx-summarize/src` is the whole `ctx-summarize` crate: it walks a
context tree bottom-up and (re)writes `.ctx` leaf/rollup summary files by
calling an LLM-backed agent, gated by access control and scope limits. A
caller depending on this crate gets one entry point of real consequence —
`cli::dispatch` / `runner::run` — plus a stable `.context` mirror layout
(`cpath`) and a `SummError` enum every fallible path returns through.

The crate enforces a strict seam layering: `cli` only parses argv and
writes output; `runner` is pure orchestration and must never touch
`std::fs` or spawn a process directly — all such effects go through the
`Fs` and `Agent` traits (`fs.rs`, `agent.rs`), which is also what makes
`runner` unit-testable with fakes. `progress.rs` is a third, optional seam
in the same style, invoked by `runner` just before each `Agent::complete`
call. Prompt text is never a Rust string literal — `runner::load_prompts`
reads `summarizer-leaf.md`/`summarizer-rollup.md` from the prompts dir at
runtime, and `intent.md` is read but never written anywhere in this crate.

Two format contracts span files here and must be changed together:
`assemble_rollup_input` in `runner.rs` builds the section-labeled
prompt input consumed by `summarizer-rollup.md`; and `agent.rs`'s
stdin/stdout JSON wire format is the boundary any `CTX_AGENT_CMD` script
must match. `cpath.rs` defines the `.context` mirror mapping used by both
`runner` (to compute leaf/rollup paths) and `cli`/`main` indirectly; it
intentionally duplicates equivalent logic in `ctx-context`, tracked as a
known drift risk in `docs/UNIMPLEMENTED.md`. `fs.rs`'s `scope_matcher`
(`.ctxignore`-based) is the single scope definition shared with
`ctx-scan`'s walker — keep both in sync on change.

Invariants holding across the whole subtree: every fallible path returns
`SummError` (no `#[from]` conversions — callers construct variants
explicitly); `--approve`/`MAX_TARGETS` gating and `AccessDenied` checks
happen before any file is read or agent is called; and `main.rs` /
`cli.rs` never write ad-hoc output — only through injected writer handles,
keeping stdout reserved for the final JSON result.